    question: "Do I need a Facebook Business page?",
    answer: "A Facebook Business page with Messenger enabled is the requirement — personal accounts cannot be connected. Most tree surgery businesses already have a Facebook presence where they post completed work and gather reviews. If your page is basic, the AI still handles incoming messages with full professionalism on your behalf."
  },
  {
    question: "What tree surgery enquiries come through Messenger?",
    answer: "Almost exclusively domestic — homeowners who have seen your work through a neighbour's recommendation, a community group reference, or a local search. Typical requests involve tree pruning, felling, stump grinding, hedge reduction, and occasionally emergency storm damage. The homeowners who message through Facebook tend to be further along in their decision process because they have already seen your work."
  },
  {
    question: "How quickly does the AI reply?",
    answer: "Within seconds. Facebook Messenger shows active indicators and read receipts, so the homeowner sees immediate engagement from your business. In tree surgery — where three or four companies typically receive the same enquiry — the speed of the first professional reply frequently determines who gets the site visit."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does Facebook Messenger cost?",
    answer: `Messenger is available at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as an add-on to the Core plan. For tree surgery companies where the average domestic job is worth £400 to £2,000, capturing one client through a prompt Messenger reply covers the annual add-on cost comfortably.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I reply to Messenger conversations myself?",
    answer: "Sending your own message in any thread transfers control to you. The AI steps aside and the homeowner sees one continuous conversation. Most tree surgeons let the AI handle the initial response and species identification, then follow up personally with access questions, pricing, and scheduling."
  },
  {
    question: "How is Messenger data protected?",
    answer: "All Messenger conversations, tree photos, property addresses, and contact details are encrypted and held on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Data is delivered only to you and is never used for advertising, sold to aggregators, or accessed by anyone outside your business."
